my son is starting kindergarten in two weeks i'm nervous excited any tips as a mom and retired kindergarten teacher assistant and personal aid to special needs children i can tell you this get him used to the idea of being away from you help him choose a pencil box that you can tape a picture of you and him inside of this will help him on those first few days when he misses you the most tell him that you want him to bring the picture home when he thinks he is ready to do that teach hime to spell his name and recognize it teach hime his address and a phone number you can be reached at as well take him to the orientation night and allow him to get to know the teacher and see where his room and table will be on the first day even though it is the hardest thing to do walk him into his class help him find his seat and say your goodbyes do not linger even if he cries just hug him and tell him you will be there as soon as the bell rings to come home if he rides a bus be sure to pin a note to his back pack that has your address and phone number as well as his bus route or number Avenue Q The Adventures of Pete & Pete The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Miss Saigon Education in Germany The Inside Kindergarten Mad Money The Star Wars Holiday Special Professional wrestling match types Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Jon Secada Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Dog training Grandview, U.S.A. Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Social rule The Dalek Invasion of Earth University of Massachusetts Amherst Columbine High School massacre Trish Stratus Rent (musical) Lauren Bacall Piccolo Junior Saga Kodocha Teachers (film) Bus models used in New York City Transit Bart chalkboard gags The Ashlee Simpson Show Good Times The Jazz Singer Friends Characters of Lost Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Education in the United States Database management system Education The Emancipation of Mimi Education in Romania A Course In Miracles Harley Davidson and the Marlboro Man CPU cache C